<article
  class="card card-elsewhere card-linked"
  data-edit-this="news/2023/05/2023-05-16-why-vote-gov-supports-multiple-languages.md"
  
  aria-labelledby="title-why-vote.gov-supports-multiple-languages"
>
  <div class="card__content">
    <div class="card__summary">
      <h3 id="title-why-vote.gov-supports-multiple-languages">
        <a href="/2023/05/16/why-vote-gov-supports-multiple-languages/">Why vote.gov supports multiple languages</a>
      </h3>
      <p>According to a 2019 U.S. Census Bureau survey, nearly 68 million people in the U.S. speak a language other than English at home. To help make the voting process accessible to everyone who is eligible, vote.gov works with state election offices, federal agencies, and non-partisan organizations to create a national source of accurate voting information and clear registration instructions in multiple languages.
          <em class="card__source source"
            >— via
            <a
              href="https://blog.usa.gov/why-vote.gov-supports-multiple-languages"
              title="Read at USA.gov"
              >USA.gov</a
            ></em
          >
        
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card__media">
    <img src="/logos/usagov-logo.png" alt="USA.gov logo" />
  </div>
  <div class="card__meta">
    <p class="date">May 16, 2023</p>
  </div>
</article>

            
              
                
                
  






